14/12/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- The IMF decided on Wednesday (13 December) to clear $1 billion in new loans to Turkey under a three-year $10 billion standby agreement. The Fund praised Turkey's "sound policy framework" and its efforts to curb inflation. Experts were impressed by the Turkish Central Bank's "decisive response" to turbulence in the financial markets in May and June. The IMF also approved Turkey's request for waivers on several performance criteria. (Dow Jones, AFP - 13/12/06) 
